abstract: The company reported quarterly net income of $1.86 billion on growing demand for personal computers.
snippet: The company reported quarterly net income of $1.86 billion on growing demand for personal computers.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, Oct. 16  After raising its revenue forecast for the quarter last month, Intel did not disappoint investors today when it reported even better-than-expected sales and profits on growing demand for personal computers.

headline.main: Intel Exceeds Estimates With 43% Earnings Rise
